Mexico Stocks: Elektra, Inbursa Shares Advance; Penoles Drops

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-07-01T20:44:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/mexico-stocks-elektra-inbursa-shares-advance-penoles-drops.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.7 percent to 36,800.72.  Retailers and banks were among the biggest gainers on
Mexico’s benchmark index after U.S. manufacturing unexpectedly
expanded at a faster pace in June, a sign that industry is
rebounding in Mexico’s biggest export market. The Institute for
Supply Management’s factory index rose to 55.3 last month from
53.5 in May, the Tempe, Arizona-based group said today.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA* MM), the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , jumped 3.8
percent to 625.68 pesos.  Grupo Financiero Inbursa SA (GFINBURO)  , the financial services firm controlled by billionaire
 Carlos Slim , gained 2.8 percent to 61.60 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, declined 0.1 percent to 441 pesos. Silver
futures for September delivery fell as much as 3.9 percent to
$33.47 an ounce on the Comex in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
